  "text": "Envoy proxy implements comprehensive HTTP request header injection prevention through multiple layers of validation and sanitization across the codebase.\n\n## Core Header Validation Architecture\n\nThe primary validation framework is defined in `envoy/http/header_validator.h`, which provides interfaces for `HeaderValidator`, `ServerHeaderValidator`, and `ClientHeaderValidator`. The `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/header_validator.cc` implements the base validation logic with methods for:\n\n- `validateGenericHeaderName()` (line 173-222): Validates header names against RFC 9110 token rules, including enforcement of underscore rejection based on configuration\n- `validateGenericHeaderValue()` (line 224-252): Validates header values against RFC 9110 field-vchar rules\n- `validateMethodHeader()` (line 42-114): Validates HTTP method tokens against IANA registry\n- `validateSchemeHeader()` (line 116-137): Validates http/https schemes\n- `validateHostHeader()` (line 278-333): Validates host headers with IPv6/IPv4 and deprecated userinfo detection (line 290-301)\n- `validatePathHeaderCharacters()` (line 423-427): Validates URI path characters\n- `validateTrailers()` (line 602-629): Validates trailer headers\n\n## Protocol-Specific Validators\n\n**HTTP/1 Validation** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http1_header_validator.cc`):\n- Implements HTTP/1.1 specific validation per RFC 9112\n- Validates transfer-encoding headers\n- Uses protocol-specific character tables\n\n**HTTP/2 Validation** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http2_header_validator.cc`):\n- Implements HTTP/2 specific validation per RFC 9113\n- Validates pseudo-headers (:method, :authority, :scheme, :path)\n- Rejects Connection headers per HTTP/2 spec\n- Enforces TE header restrictions\n\n## Header Sanitization and Forbidden Headers\n\n**Internal Header Stripping** (`source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc`, lines 134-144):\nThe connection manager explicitly removes internal and proxy headers:\n- `request_headers.removeConnection()`: Removes Connection header\n- `request_headers.removeUpgrade()`: Removes Upgrade header  \n- `request_headers.removeEnvoyInternalRequest()`: Removes x-envoy-internal header\n- `request_headers.removeKeepAlive()`: Removes Keep-Alive header\n- `request_headers.removeProxyConnection()`: Removes Proxy-Connection header\n- `request_headers.removeTransferEncoding()`: Removes Transfer-Encoding\n\nThese removals are only performed on first pass (line 1498 of `conn_manager_impl.cc`): `if (!state_.is_internally_created_)` to prevent double-sanitization.\n\n**Connection Header Sanitization** (`source/common/http/utility.cc`, lines 932-1031):\nThe `Utility::sanitizeConnectionHeader()` function implements hop-by-hop header validation that:\n- Limits nominated headers to maximum 10 (line 947)\n- Prevents nomination of X-Forwarded-* headers (line 982-984) which could mask request origin per security guidance\n- Prevents nomination of pseudo-headers (line 985)\n- Enforces TE header size limits (MAX_ALLOWED_TE_VALUE_SIZE = 256 bytes)\n- Removes unsupported TE values, keeping only \"trailers\"\n\n**Path Sanitization** (`source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/header_validator.cc`):\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()` (line 655-662): Removes URL fragments\n- `sanitizeEncodedSlashes()` (line 665-695): Handles escaped slashes based on configuration\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()` (line 631-653): Drops headers with underscores per config\n- `encodeAdditionalCharactersInPath()` (line 487-542): Encodes non-compliant characters in URI paths\n\n## Internal Header Definitions\n\nThe file `source/common/http/headers.h` defines all internal headers used throughout Envoy, including:\n- `EnvoyInternalRequest` (line 168): Marks internally-generated requests\n- Forwarded headers: `ForwardedFor`, `ForwardedHost`, `ForwardedProto`, `ForwardedPort`, `ForwardedClientCert` (lines 143-200)\n- Other internal headers: `EnvoyCluster`, `EnvoyAttemptCount`, `EnvoyExternalAddress`, etc.\n\n## Character Validation\n\nThe `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/character_tables.h` provides bit-mapped character tables for validating:\n- Token characters (tchar) for header names\n- Field-vchar for header values\n- URI path and query characters\n- IPv6 address characters\n- Regular domain name (reg-name) characters\n\n## Error Handling\n\nValidation failures are tracked with detailed error codes defined in `envoy/http/header_validator_errors.h`:\n- `InvalidNameCharacters`: Invalid header name characters\n- `InvalidValueCharacters`: Invalid header value characters\n- `InvalidHost`: Host header validation failure\n- `InvalidPseudoHeader`: Unknown pseudo-header\n- `EmptyHeaderName`: Empty header name\n- `InvalidUnderscore`: Underscore in header name\n- Protocol-specific errors: `InvalidTransferEncoding`, `ChunkedContentLength`\n\n## Prevention Mechanisms\n\nThe header injection prevention is enforced through:\n\n1. **Validation at Parse Time**: HTTP codec implementations validate headers as they are parsed\n2. **Sanitization at Forwarding**: Connection manager removes sensitive internal/proxy headers before upstream transmission\n3. **Configuration Control**: Headers with underscores, fragments in paths, and transfer-encoding can be configured as reject/drop/allow\n4. **Userinfo Detection**: Deprecated RFC userinfo in authority headers is explicitly rejected (line 297-301)\n5. **Hop-by-Hop Header Protection**: X-Forwarded-* headers cannot be nominated in Connection header\n6. **RFC Compliance**: Strict validation against RFC 9110 (HTTP Semantics), RFC 9112 (HTTP/1.1), and RFC 9113 (HTTP/2)\n"
